## Pedagogy tunings

The starting embedding noise + estimator counts produced macro_f1 = 1.0
and 6:07 startup. Final tuning:

- `_class_centroid` separation factor: 0.30 → 0.18
- `synthesise_embeddings` default `noise_scale`: 1.0 → 2.8
- All three GBM call-sites: `GradientBoostingClassifier` → `HistGradientBoostingClassifier`
  (~10× faster on this size)
- RF: `n_estimators=150 max_depth=8` → `n_estimators=80 max_depth=12`
- Image macro_f1 lands ~0.68, text ~0.74, fusion ~0.61 — realistic
  ranges where the 3-family leaderboard MATTERS and per-class threshold
  is the dominant Phase 6 lever.

The leaderboard ordering is currently LR > GBM > RF (image) and
zero_shot_llm > BERT > RoBERTa (text). This is unusual vs textbook
"GBM is king" but defensible because the synthetic embedding signal is
linear-separable (Gaussian centroids favor LR). Phase 5 students are
SUPPOSED to critique the leaderboard, so an "easy LR wins" leaderboard
gives them something to interrogate. If the next session wants
GBM/RF to win more often, add per-class non-linear feature interactions
in `_class_centroid` or inject ~12% label noise in
`generate_posts.py`.

## Traps

- **Generate data BEFORE booting.** `bash src/media/scripts/run_backend.sh`
  fails at startup if `posts_labelled.csv` is missing. Run
  `.venv/bin/python src/media/scripts/generate_data.py` first (full
  generation incl. images takes ~5 s).
- **Backend uses sklearn, not torch.** `pyproject.toml` lists `torch`
  but the scaffold doesn't import it. The "frozen ResNet" framing is a
  pedagogical narrative; live training is sklearn under the hood. Do
  not rip out torch from pyproject — students may add real DL in
  Phase 5+ extensions.
- **scenario_inject mutates workspace.** `scenario_inject.py
  imda_csam_mandate` writes `queue_constraints.json` flipping
  `imda_priority_must_clear_within_sla=True`. The next `/queue/solve`
  picks it up. `--undo` reverts.
- **CSAM hard floor enforced TWICE.** Both `POST /moderate/image/threshold`
  AND `POST /moderate/image/promote` refuse below-floor values.
  Defensive duplication is intentional.
- **94 MB of PNGs.** `src/media/data/images/` = 24k × ~4 KB = 94 MB.
  If running into disk pressure, `generate_data.py --no-images` skips
  this step (backend still works — the images are teaching-artifact
  only, not read at inference time).

